1
00:00:10,967 --> 00:00:13,833
<i>Dad, we still have a lot to fix.</i>

2
00:00:13,967 --> 00:00:15,833
<i>We still have to talk to mom,
right?</i>

3
00:00:15,967 --> 00:00:16,967
<i> Where's mom?</i>

4
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,267
<i> Why don't we have a duel?</i>

5
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:21,733
<i> Whoever wins gets Danilo.</i>

6
00:00:21,867 --> 00:00:25,667
<i>So once you lose,
you will leave my family alone.</i>

7
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:27,233
<i> Winner takes all.</i>

8
00:00:29,933 --> 00:00:33,467
<i>I will bury you
before you get a chance!</i>

9
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:34,700
<i>Are you going to eat
that dog food?</i>

10
00:00:34,867 --> 00:00:36,533
<i>Or should I feed you
this bullet?</i>

11
00:00:36,667 --> 00:00:40,100
<i>Fine! I just want to feel loved.</i>

12
00:00:40,233 --> 00:00:43,733
<i>To be loved by Danilo and
Mookie, is that wrong to ask?</i>

13
00:00:43,867 --> 00:00:45,567
<i> Don't I deserve some love?</i>

14
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,467
<i> Stealing is a sin.</i>

15
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:50,233
<i>In God's eyes and man's law,
you know that it's wrong!</i>

16
00:00:50,367 --> 00:00:51,600
<i>- Mom?
- Emma!</i>

17
00:00:51,733 --> 00:00:52,633
<i> Emma, put the gun down!</i>

18
00:00:52,767 --> 00:00:56,467
<i>Mookie, look at what
she's doing to me!</i>

19
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,300
Mookie!

20
00:01:33,433 --> 00:01:36,800
Mookie, look at what your mom
is doing to me!

21
00:01:36,933 --> 00:01:38,367
- Emma, put the gun down!
- Look at what she's doing!

22
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:40,000
Emma, don't shoot her!

23
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:41,833
She wants to kill me!

24
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,667
Look, she even
has an accomplice!

25
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,233
Liar!

26
00:01:45,367 --> 00:01:48,000
You call that guy
to kill me off!

27
00:01:48,133 --> 00:01:50,000
No, that's not true!

28
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:53,567
Mom, but you're the one
who's holding the gun.

29
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:55,500
Mookie, let me explain.

30
00:01:55,633 --> 00:01:57,767
She brought me here
to mess with me.

31
00:01:57,900 --> 00:02:00,333
She even made me eat dog food!
Look at what she did!

32
00:02:00,467 --> 00:02:04,667
She wanted me to beg
because she wanted to kill me!

33
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:07,033
Tell her the truth!
Look at what you did!

34
00:02:07,167 --> 00:02:08,933
Mom, what is going on?

35
00:02:10,300 --> 00:02:13,800
I came here because Uncle Wiro
and Aunt Kutsy told me

36
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:16,033
that you two
are having a duel.

37
00:02:16,167 --> 00:02:17,600
A challenge.

38
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:18,500
- Mom...
- Mookie...

39
00:02:18,633 --> 00:02:21,167
Mookie, we have to talk.
Just you and me.

40
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:24,500
Listen to me, please.
Don't be upset with me.

41
00:02:24,633 --> 00:02:26,600
Please, let's talk.

42
00:02:26,733 --> 00:02:27,333
Mookie.

43
00:02:27,467 --> 00:02:28,233
Don't believe anything

44
00:02:28,367 --> 00:02:29,500
- she has to say, Mookie.
- Mookie.

45
00:02:29,633 --> 00:02:30,400
Mookie.

46
00:02:30,533 --> 00:02:33,733
I don't know
what to believe anymore.

47
00:02:33,867 --> 00:02:35,067
You know what, Mom,

48
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:37,733
I almost believed
what dad told me.

49
00:02:37,867 --> 00:02:39,900
About everything that
happened to you.

50
00:02:40,033 --> 00:02:41,800
That he might be right.

51
00:02:41,933 --> 00:02:45,900
Mookie, don't believe her!
She wants to hurt me.

52
00:02:46,033 --> 00:02:47,533
Look at her.

53
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:49,267
Mom...

54
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,600
Mom, I'm sorry.

55
00:02:51,733 --> 00:02:53,700
But...

56
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:56,000
after everything I saw.

57
00:02:56,133 --> 00:02:59,400
I don't think that dad
is telling the truth.

58
00:02:59,533 --> 00:03:00,500
Mookie.

59
00:03:01,033 --> 00:03:02,633
Mookie, let's talk.

60
00:03:02,767 --> 00:03:04,133
Mookie!

61
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:13,067
What now?

62
00:03:14,867 --> 00:03:16,333
How does it feel...

63
00:03:18,067 --> 00:03:21,867
to get rejected
by your own daughter?

64
00:03:22,033 --> 00:03:25,200
Nothing can be more painful
than that. Right, Emma?

65
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:28,400
No matter how hard you try
to get close to her,

66
00:03:28,533 --> 00:03:31,300
she will keep rejecting you.

67
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:33,667
What did you say again?

68
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,800
How does it feel?

69
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:39,567
Now tell me,

70
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:43,500
how does it feel to get treated
like garbage?

71
00:03:43,633 --> 00:03:46,233
Like an animal?

72
00:03:55,167 --> 00:03:56,467
Mookie!

73
00:04:12,667 --> 00:04:14,533
Where could Flor be?

74
00:04:15,733 --> 00:04:17,500
She's not in the office.

75
00:04:29,567 --> 00:04:30,633
Logan?

76
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,000
Logan?

77
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:38,967
Flor!

78
00:04:42,367 --> 00:04:43,200
Flor?

79
00:04:47,567 --> 00:04:48,367
Flor!

80
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,133
- Hey, Emma!
- Hurry!

81
00:04:50,267 --> 00:04:51,400
- Have you been here long?
- Water.

82
00:04:51,533 --> 00:04:52,367
Get me some water.

83
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,433
- And a towel for Logan.
- Water and towel.

84
00:04:54,567 --> 00:04:56,967
- Yes, hurry up!
- Okay, give me a minute!

85
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:03,500
What happened to him?

86
00:05:03,633 --> 00:05:05,233
- He's drunk.
- Here you go.

87
00:05:05,367 --> 00:05:06,200
Here.

88
00:05:10,867 --> 00:05:12,367
- Thank you.
- It's okay.

89
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:13,833
You can go now.
I'll take care of him.

90
00:05:13,967 --> 00:05:14,867
Okay, don't you need
anything else?

91
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,467
- I'm good.
- Okay.

92
00:05:20,733 --> 00:05:22,067
I want to drink more.

93
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:23,400
You had enough.

94
00:05:23,533 --> 00:05:24,600
Last one.

95
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,033
Emma...

96
00:05:40,533 --> 00:05:42,133
I dreamt about you.

97
00:05:45,267 --> 00:05:46,933
In my dreams...

98
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:50,100
you told me that you love me.

99
00:05:52,067 --> 00:05:53,767
And we're happy together.

100
00:05:56,367 --> 00:05:58,567
I wish I never woke up.

101
00:06:00,133 --> 00:06:02,600
I didn't want
you to see me like this.

102
00:06:04,033 --> 00:06:05,433
I admit...

103
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,633
I can take anything but...

104
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:15,000
it hurts.

105
00:06:16,033 --> 00:06:17,767
It hurts so much.

106
00:06:19,067 --> 00:06:21,033
This damn heart.

107
00:06:25,100 --> 00:06:27,600
I wish my heart
would stop beating.

108
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,500
I hope for it
to stop working

109
00:06:32,633 --> 00:06:35,633
so I won't have to feel
this pain.

110
00:06:38,067 --> 00:06:39,333
I can't bear it.

111
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:45,933
Emma, please don't leave me.

112
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:49,300
Stay by my side...

113
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:51,467
please.

114
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:59,533
Logan, if only you'll give me
a chance to take care of you...

115
00:07:00,567 --> 00:07:02,067
as a friend.

116
00:07:03,933 --> 00:07:06,300
I wouldn't have to avoid you.

117
00:07:07,367 --> 00:07:08,600
I'm sorry if...

118
00:07:10,267 --> 00:07:14,833
I can't love you back.

119
00:07:22,433 --> 00:07:25,533
Mookie, Wiro and Kutsy
told me about what happened.

120
00:07:25,667 --> 00:07:28,400
They said your Aunt Jade
and Emma had a fight again.

121
00:07:29,433 --> 00:07:32,833
Dad, I'm sorry
if I didn't tell you about it.

122
00:07:32,967 --> 00:07:35,700
I didn't want you to worry.

123
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:39,467
And you have to regain
your strength.

124
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,967
You should have told me...

125
00:07:43,133 --> 00:07:46,167
I could have been there
and stopped them.

126
00:07:47,433 --> 00:07:48,900
But you know what, Mookie...

127
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:51,867
it's all my fault.

128
00:07:53,467 --> 00:07:55,867
I let my emotions control me.

129
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:00,067
I shouldn't have let
your Aunt Jade fall for me.

130
00:08:01,133 --> 00:08:03,133
I shouldn't have hurt
both of them.

131
00:08:03,267 --> 00:08:04,600
- Your Mommy Emma...
- Dad.

132
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,900
But, Dad...

133
00:08:08,033 --> 00:08:10,333
why is mom acting that way?

134
00:08:11,167 --> 00:08:13,700
She changed a lot.

135
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:15,967
You know what, Dad,

136
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:18,267
I saw how much
she hated Aunt Jade

137
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:20,267
while pointing a gun at her.

138
00:08:22,133 --> 00:08:23,200
What if I was right

139
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:27,467
when I said that she's becoming
like Mommy Olive?

140
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,600
That will never happen.

141
00:08:32,167 --> 00:08:33,767
I know that you're confused
right now.

142
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,233
But I hope...

143
00:08:36,367 --> 00:08:38,300
you'll try to understand
your mom.

144
00:08:39,467 --> 00:08:42,200
Please give her...

145
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:43,667
a chance...

146
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:46,267
to explain herself.

147
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:47,567
Okay?

148
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:54,167
We didn't get to talk as a
family because of the accident.

149
00:08:55,767 --> 00:08:57,100
But I promise you,

150
00:08:57,233 --> 00:09:01,967
the three of us will talk when
I get out of this hospital.

151
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:04,900
You, me, and your Mommy Emma.

152
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,433
So gross!

153
00:09:21,633 --> 00:09:24,667
That Emma is cockcroach level
nightmare!

154
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:27,133
Never did I imagine
that I would eat dog food

155
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:30,100
like a stray dog!

156
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:36,333
That's what you get
from challenging her!

157
00:09:36,467 --> 00:09:38,033
I was ready!

158
00:09:38,167 --> 00:09:39,300
Fully armed!

159
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:43,067
Fully fab with a backup plan!

160
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:46,767
I was so ready to punish her!

161
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:48,800
But little did I know...

162
00:09:48,933 --> 00:09:52,367
that Emma knows martial arts!

163
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:54,800
She even pointed a gun at me!

164
00:09:54,933 --> 00:09:56,100
A gun!

165
00:09:56,233 --> 00:09:57,467
Can you believe that, Leticia?

166
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,300
Did she think
we were in an action movie?

167
00:09:59,433 --> 00:10:02,033
Now I feel like
I'm such a sore loser!

168
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:11,133
Hello, Caloy.

169
00:10:11,267 --> 00:10:14,633
Make sure you have something
good to tell me, or else...

170
00:10:14,767 --> 00:10:17,367
An officer is waiting
outside the house.

171
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:19,300
He's with the guy
Ligaya's acquainted with.

172
00:10:19,433 --> 00:10:21,400
<i>I think they're here for Ligaya.</i>

173
00:10:21,533 --> 00:10:22,733
What?

174
00:10:22,867 --> 00:10:24,400
Okay, we'll be on our way there.

175
00:10:25,433 --> 00:10:27,133
We need to head home right now.

176
00:10:27,267 --> 00:10:29,067
They can't find out
about Ligaya.

177
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,400
Hurry up!

178
00:10:36,533 --> 00:10:38,267
You're lucky, Ador...

179
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:39,867
that I feel bad for you.

180
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,867
But...

181
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,367
are you sure about this?

182
00:10:45,433 --> 00:10:47,600
You could be wrong.

183
00:10:47,733 --> 00:10:49,167
We'll get in trouble if you are.

184
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:51,767
I can't be wrong about this!
I heard her there!

185
00:10:53,067 --> 00:10:57,267
She could have starved by now.

186
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:59,633
What if she's unconscious?

187
00:10:59,767 --> 00:11:00,767
Okay, let's check.

188
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:04,100
Where is the path
that leads to her?

189
00:11:04,233 --> 00:11:05,233
Over this way.

190
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:08,033
Ador!

191
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,767
- It's this way!
- Be careful, Ador!

192
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:13,233
- It's here. I'm sure of it!
- You'll get hurt, Ador!

193
00:11:13,367 --> 00:11:14,733
I went through this path.

194
00:11:14,867 --> 00:11:16,567
Ador, calm down.

195
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:18,233
What you're doing is dangerous!

196
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:43,867
<i> Dear God...</i>

197
00:11:45,567 --> 00:11:49,000
<i>I know that I tried
to escape many times.</i>

198
00:11:51,267 --> 00:11:53,200
<i> But please,</i>

199
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:55,567
<i> please help me this time.</i>

200
00:11:58,100 --> 00:12:01,700
<i>But if I wouldn't make it
out alive,</i>

201
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:06,833
<i>I'm begging you to ease my pain.</i>

202
00:12:06,967 --> 00:12:10,133
<i>And I hope that you can
see my will to live.</i>

203
00:12:11,233 --> 00:12:13,833
<i>Especially now
that I found my husband.</i>

204
00:12:14,933 --> 00:12:18,000
<i>Now that I have a reason
to fight.</i>

205
00:12:19,133 --> 00:12:23,733
<i>So, I will never stop
until I get out of this place.</i>

206
00:12:39,933 --> 00:12:40,900
Ligaya?

207
00:12:44,233 --> 00:12:45,333
Ligaya?

208
00:12:49,467 --> 00:12:50,700
Ligaya!

209
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:54,067
Ligaya!

210
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,533
Where is your wife?

211
00:12:57,433 --> 00:12:59,900
There's not even a sign
of a cage or cabinet around.

212
00:13:02,367 --> 00:13:04,767
It only means one thing.

213
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:06,833
They know that we're coming.

214
00:13:06,967 --> 00:13:08,600
They moved her out of here.

215
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:17,633
Good thing
Caloy got you out of there.

216
00:13:17,767 --> 00:13:23,067
And clean up your mess
before your lover gets there.

217
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:33,733
In fairness, you still
have a lot of spirit.

218
00:13:37,367 --> 00:13:38,400
What was that?

219
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:42,100
What about Ador?

220
00:13:43,167 --> 00:13:45,000
Is he safe?

221
00:13:45,133 --> 00:13:46,867
Is your father safe?

222
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,467
Oh, please...

223
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:55,467
can you stop this nonsense?

224
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:59,333
I don't have a father.

225
00:14:01,267 --> 00:14:03,467
And if he doesn't stop
pestering me,

226
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:07,767
I'll make sure
that he'll pay for it.

227
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,067
No matter what you say...

228
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:15,533
he is still your father.

229
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:17,700
His name is Ador.

230
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:21,233
No matter how many times
you reject the truth.

231
00:14:21,367 --> 00:14:24,700
You can never change the fact
that Ador...

232
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:26,767
is your father.

233
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:31,367
I said, shut up!

234
00:14:31,533 --> 00:14:34,400
Why can't you understand...

235
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:38,667
that I don't have a father!

236
00:14:42,667 --> 00:14:43,700
You know what...

237
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,667
in fairness to you...

238
00:14:47,733 --> 00:14:50,433
I'm impressed
with your willpower.

239
00:14:51,967 --> 00:14:53,533
You kept escaping.

240
00:14:54,567 --> 00:14:56,733
Don't you see it?

241
00:14:57,867 --> 00:15:01,000
I keep capturing you back.

242
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:03,800
Because, Ligaya...

243
00:15:07,133 --> 00:15:09,500
you can never escape from me.

244
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:13,300
Because you can never escape...

245
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:17,633
what you did to me.

246
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:22,500
No matter
how many times you escape...

247
00:15:24,467 --> 00:15:25,867
I'll make sure...

248
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:29,967
you'll end up here with me!

249
00:15:37,633 --> 00:15:40,500
Even if I had to crawl.

250
00:15:40,633 --> 00:15:43,767
Even if I can't move anymore.

251
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:45,400
I will never give up.

252
00:15:47,067 --> 00:15:51,800
I will do everything
to escape this hell hole.

253
00:15:51,933 --> 00:15:55,300
Even though I'm here
with my own daughter.

254
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,267
And aside from trying to escape,

255
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:04,567
I also did my best
to understand you.

256
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:07,567
I always tell myself...

257
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:09,200
that you might listen to me

258
00:16:09,367 --> 00:16:15,167
when I beg you over
and over to forgive me.

259
00:16:15,300 --> 00:16:18,433
Let me make it up to you.

260
00:16:18,567 --> 00:16:21,633
That I love you.

261
00:16:21,767 --> 00:16:24,700
I'm still hoping that
you will forgive me someday.

262
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:26,033
That you will understand
where I'm coming from.

263
00:16:26,167 --> 00:16:29,167
That you will accept me
as your mother.

264
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:33,967
No matter how much
you beg for forgiveness.

265
00:16:36,100 --> 00:16:38,400
It will never happen.

266
00:16:40,767 --> 00:16:42,700
Because since
I was a little child...

267
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,100
I promised myself...

268
00:16:50,567 --> 00:16:56,633
that I would never forgive you
for abandoning me and Jade.

269
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:01,867
I will never forget
what you did, Ligaya!

270
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:04,533
If that's the case,
just let me go!

271
00:17:08,567 --> 00:17:11,933
Set me free from this hell hole!

272
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:16,767
I will go as far as I can
so you will never see me again.

273
00:17:16,933 --> 00:17:19,167
I will be out of your life.

274
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:21,667
So I can be with Emma.

275
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:24,367
Since she's the only one
who accepts me as her mother.

276
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:27,467
Because she's the only child
that you raised as your own!

277
00:17:28,633 --> 00:17:29,967
You're right.

278
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:37,567
Your favorite child
should join you in hell!

279
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:39,467
Because that's where you belong.

280
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:40,400
You're a monster!

281
00:17:40,533 --> 00:17:42,933
I don't need a sister!

282
00:17:43,067 --> 00:17:46,433
And I don't need a mother!

283
00:17:51,933 --> 00:17:55,667
I will never forgive you,
Ligaya.

284
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:58,100
And you deserve...

285
00:17:58,233 --> 00:18:00,633
to rot in here!

286
00:18:01,367 --> 00:18:06,067
This is a light punishment
compared to what you did to me.

287
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:07,867
This is nothing.

288
00:18:25,367 --> 00:18:26,200
Emma,

289
00:18:27,133 --> 00:18:29,633
I'm sorry if I was so drunk
last night.

290
00:18:31,367 --> 00:18:33,833
I heard...

291
00:18:33,967 --> 00:18:35,633
I almost fell down.

292
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:38,967
It was possible that...

293
00:18:40,467 --> 00:18:43,300
if you weren't there,
I would have bashed my head in.

294
00:18:43,433 --> 00:18:46,467
You were there
to take care of me, so...

295
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:49,467
thank you.

296
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:55,067
Logan, we're still friends.

297
00:18:55,233 --> 00:18:57,233
We had history.

298
00:18:57,367 --> 00:18:59,667
Taking care of you
is the right thing to do.

299
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:04,900
I'm good with that.

300
00:19:06,933 --> 00:19:08,500
As long as we're still friends.

301
00:19:10,567 --> 00:19:11,733
You know what,

302
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:14,567
I had a dream last night.

303
00:19:16,600 --> 00:19:20,367
When I woke up,
I realized that...

304
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:23,733
I should be content
with what you're willing to give

305
00:19:23,867 --> 00:19:25,333
to this relationship.

306
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,967
Like our friendship.

307
00:19:30,567 --> 00:19:32,067
For me...

308
00:19:33,467 --> 00:19:35,433
I just want you to be happy.

309
00:19:38,667 --> 00:19:40,400
Logan...

310
00:19:40,533 --> 00:19:42,600
I'm glad you understand.

311
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,733
Don't worry,

312
00:19:45,867 --> 00:19:48,000
you'll find someone to love you.

313
00:19:49,067 --> 00:19:52,433
You will be happy
with whoever is meant for you.

314
00:19:55,633 --> 00:19:56,867
Thank you.

315
00:19:59,133 --> 00:20:00,567
Excuse me.

316
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:03,700
Hello?

317
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,333
Boss...

318
00:20:11,467 --> 00:20:13,200
did I hear it right?

319
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:14,900
You're letting her go?

320
00:20:15,033 --> 00:20:16,833
I was just pretending.

321
00:20:16,967 --> 00:20:18,833
Are you serious?

322
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:21,600
I'm not stupid to let Emma go.

323
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:26,833
Especially now that she showed
me how caring she is.

324
00:20:28,067 --> 00:20:29,967
To be truly loved by her.

325
00:20:33,133 --> 00:20:36,133
That's why no matter
who I meet...

326
00:20:37,867 --> 00:20:41,333
they're no match
for the love I have for Emma.

327
00:20:42,367 --> 00:20:44,833
What are you going to do now,
Sir?

328
00:20:44,967 --> 00:20:47,200
She only sees you as a friend.

329
00:20:48,700 --> 00:20:51,400
Then we'll ask Cupid to help us.

330
00:20:52,533 --> 00:20:55,600
And if that's not enough,
there's still one more...

331
00:20:55,733 --> 00:20:58,533
we can ask Satan for help.

332
00:21:00,033 --> 00:21:03,400
That way, she wouldn't have
a choice but to love me.

333
00:21:13,700 --> 00:21:15,800
We have to stop now, Ador.

334
00:21:15,933 --> 00:21:18,767
There's not even a trace
of blood

335
00:21:18,900 --> 00:21:21,133
or any scratches
on the furniture.

336
00:21:21,267 --> 00:21:22,467
And...

337
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:25,533
she's not in any possible places
that they could have hidden her.

338
00:21:27,467 --> 00:21:29,700
We have to try one last time,
Martinez.

339
00:21:29,833 --> 00:21:33,433
We have to find
where my daughter hid my wife.

340
00:21:35,267 --> 00:21:36,333
Ador...

341
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,967
if I were you...

342
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:40,733
I would stop this search.

343
00:21:40,867 --> 00:21:42,867
Just go home.

344
00:21:43,033 --> 00:21:45,700
You might get in trouble
for trespassing.

345
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:47,667
Or stalking.

346
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:56,700
If you don't want to help me.

347
00:21:56,833 --> 00:21:58,767
Then don't!

348
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:01,200
I will look for her myself.

349
00:22:01,333 --> 00:22:04,100
I'm the only one who
cares about her anyway!

350
00:22:04,233 --> 00:22:05,967
Well...

351
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:07,600
I'm the only...

352
00:22:07,733 --> 00:22:09,733
the only...

353
00:22:09,867 --> 00:22:10,800
- Ador!
- one that loves her.

354
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:12,200
Ador!

355
00:22:15,567 --> 00:22:17,167
What's going on, Ador?

356
00:22:20,033 --> 00:22:21,400
Ador!

357
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:34,267
I just returned
from the hospital.

358
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:36,400
Are you leaving?

359
00:22:36,533 --> 00:22:37,500
Yes.

360
00:22:39,700 --> 00:22:41,367
I'm leaving for good.

361
00:22:43,367 --> 00:22:47,400
I thought you needed time
to think things through?

362
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:48,900
About our situation.

363
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:52,333
I thought you needed time to...

364
00:22:52,467 --> 00:22:54,033
accept that...

365
00:22:55,733 --> 00:22:58,333
accept that we're over.

366
00:22:58,467 --> 00:22:59,833
That's what I thought, too.

367
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:04,333
But I realized that...

368
00:23:06,300 --> 00:23:09,733
if I insist
on us being a family...

369
00:23:11,333 --> 00:23:14,633
I might end up hurting you...

370
00:23:14,767 --> 00:23:16,400
and Mookie.

371
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:20,933
I realized that...

372
00:23:22,533 --> 00:23:24,900
I didn't want
to be like Olive...

373
00:23:26,233 --> 00:23:27,500
who lost her mind...

374
00:23:28,867 --> 00:23:31,933
because she wanted to control
the people she loved.

375
00:23:35,233 --> 00:23:36,867
I don't want to be like her.

376
00:23:38,467 --> 00:23:40,500
And I will never be like her.

377
00:23:42,267 --> 00:23:43,300
So yes...

378
00:23:48,433 --> 00:23:50,300
I'm giving up on you.

379
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:54,767
Even if it hurts.

380
00:23:56,300 --> 00:23:59,467
Perhaps I just have
to accept that...

381
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:03,733
you are meant to be with Emma.

382
00:24:15,267 --> 00:24:16,567
Thank you.

383
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,500
Thank you, Jade.

384
00:24:23,633 --> 00:24:25,000
Thank you.

385
00:24:48,867 --> 00:24:51,267
Why don't you come
with me abroad?

386
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:53,100
I can get a business-class
flight for you.

387
00:24:53,233 --> 00:24:56,433
So you can be a classy loser.

388
00:24:57,600 --> 00:24:59,133
Are you serious?

389
00:24:59,267 --> 00:25:00,233
Business class?

390
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:03,067
Didn't you owe me money?

391
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:08,800
And who says I lost?
Who says I'm leaving?

392
00:25:08,933 --> 00:25:10,367
I don't run away.

393
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:15,100
In fact, I'm already planning
my next grand entrance.

394
00:25:15,233 --> 00:25:16,433
What are you talking about?

395
00:25:16,567 --> 00:25:20,367
Didn't you just tell Danilo that
you're letting him go for Emma?

396
00:25:20,500 --> 00:25:23,700
I thought you were moving on.

397
00:25:23,833 --> 00:25:25,967
Planning stage, my darling.

398
00:25:26,100 --> 00:25:29,033
I'm moving on, not moving out.

399
00:25:31,300 --> 00:25:33,033
I'm excited...

400
00:25:34,067 --> 00:25:35,633
to execute my plans.

401
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:38,400
Because my desperate era
is so over.

402
00:25:38,533 --> 00:25:40,833
And I'm ready to engage.

403
00:25:40,967 --> 00:25:42,067
I knew it!

404
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,967
That's why
you're not even bothered.

405
00:25:44,100 --> 00:25:45,200
Bothered?

406
00:25:45,333 --> 00:25:48,367
That's not
even in my dictionary.

407
00:25:48,500 --> 00:25:51,233
With the plans I have,

408
00:25:51,367 --> 00:25:56,367
I will make sure that Danilo
will beg me to come back.

409
00:25:56,500 --> 00:25:57,933
He will forget
about Emma's existence

410
00:25:58,067 --> 00:26:02,933
without me having to lift
a perfectly manicured finger.

411
00:26:10,300 --> 00:26:12,100
Danilo called off the wedding.

412
00:26:13,033 --> 00:26:15,600
He admitted that he was
still in love with Emma.

413
00:26:15,733 --> 00:26:17,400
Emma also admitted that...

414
00:26:19,167 --> 00:26:21,000
she's still in love with Danilo.

415
00:26:21,133 --> 00:26:23,333
Danilo belongs to me,

416
00:26:23,467 --> 00:26:26,300
and Emma belongs to you.

417
00:26:26,433 --> 00:26:29,933
So I think we need
to join forces.

418
00:26:30,067 --> 00:26:32,767
We need to stop them
from getting back together.

419
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:33,867
Here,

420
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:37,267
Sir Logan wants you to have this
to calm you down.

421
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:41,333
He said you seemed anxious
after talking to Danilo.

422
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:46,167
Your wickedness
will never succeed, Olive.

423
00:26:46,300 --> 00:26:48,100
Nope.

424
00:26:48,233 --> 00:26:50,233
I'll succeed.

425
00:26:50,367 --> 00:26:52,867
Danilo will marry me.

426
00:26:55,267 --> 00:26:56,000
Dan?

427
00:26:56,133 --> 00:26:58,000
Hey, Danilo, Mookie.

428
00:26:58,133 --> 00:27:00,400
Wait, where's Emma?

429
00:27:00,533 --> 00:27:02,667
She's in the office, waiting.
